wiki.content:
Judas Priest frontman Rob Halford, recording next door, stepped in for a guest spot on "Feel Good Hit of the Summer" Later in a radio interview, Homme and Nick Oliveri agreed to give the LAPD permission to use the song "Feel Good Hit of the Summer" in anti-drunk driving films in return for a reduced sentence.

track.name: Feel Good Hit of the Summer
comments: This song has a good message.

I loved how when we saw them live (and got to party backstage after the show with them!!!!!!!! ;-) ), Josh ad-libbed "TEN.... THOUSAND... Bottles of.. cough medicine...." in the break-down, right before kicking back into the final mosh!
Nicotine, valium, vicodin, marijuana... ecstasy and alcohol.
fuck yeah josh rocks in every band!
So, this song is about a highly intelligent but introverted guy trying to get by in the modern cut-throat business world, right?
